A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Juniors Running Club; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the Juniors Running Club was established in 2013 with just 40 students from
3 grades third through fifth; and
4 WHEREAS, the club currently operates out of Baldwin Elementary School in Norcross,
5 Georgia, and has grown to include approximately 100 elementary school runners, 30 middle
6 school runners, and 15 high school runners; and
7 WHEREAS, the club's teams have achieved significant competitive success, with its
8 elementary school runners winning multiple cluster races against six elementary schools in
9 the Norcross cluster and its middle school team earning numerous podium finishes since it
10 began competing in cross country in 2014; and
11 WHEREAS, the middle school runners finished the 2016 and 2019 seasons with remarkable
12 perfect season records, ranking seventh in the State of Georgia; and
