13 WHEREAS, in 2017, the Juniors Running Club was awarded the Arthur Blank Scholarship,
14 providing over 100 pairs of new Mizuno running shoes to its elementary and middle school
15 athletes; and
16 WHEREAS, the club has competed several times at the Junior Olympics Nationals and
17 Regionals, including in Birmingham, Alabama, in 2016; Tallahassee, Florida, in 2017 and
18 2019; Charleston, South Carolina, in 2018; Madison, Wisconsin, in 2019; Lexington,
19 Kentucky, in 2020 and 2021; and Louisville, Kentucky, in 2024 at the Middle School
20 Nationals; and
21 WHEREAS, the mission of the Juniors Running Club is to promote movement and fitness
22 through the sport of running, prepare runners for high school cross country and track
23 competition, and serve as ambassadors for the sport and their schools; and
24 WHEREAS, these magnificent teams have earned their well-deserved reputation for
25 excellence, and it is abundantly fitting and proper that their extraordinary accomplishments
26 be appropriately honored.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend the Juniors Running Club for its many
29 exemplary victories as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 Juniors Running Club.
